		"AbilityTooltips"
		{
			"special_bonus_lifesteal_30"		"Both spell and attack lifesteal? You will become nearly unkillable!"
			"special_bonus_attack_speed_25"		"More attack speed = more lightning procs, faster farm and higher damage output. Flux is just unreliable and not really useful in lategame."
			"special_bonus_attack_damage_30"		"Higher damage output is more valuable. You will already have enough tankiness"
			"special_bonus_cooldown_reduction_10"		"Attack range could be nice, but since we are going to be in frontline all the time, we don't need it that much, while CDR talent will decrease downtime between doubles even more"
			"arc_warden_flux"		"Even while sparks are more useful for farming, Flux is much more useful for killing people (double flux = 100% slow or 100 ms on targeted hero and a lot of damage), so you want to max out it first"
			"arc_warden_magnetic_field"		"Our strongest spell for both offensive (a lot of bonus attack speed) and defensive (save allies, yourself or even your base from being attacked) plays, altho not really useful for killing early on"
			"arc_warden_spark_wraith"		"We can spam it with octarine and aquila, it can help us out in lane so we won't get ganked, RQQEE combo will kill almost anybody in early game"
			"arc_warden_tempest_double"		"Your main trick. With double you can instakill a lot of heroes, splitfarm and be quite useful in fights. Just remember that you need as much effective slots (active items you can use twice or use without losing charges) as possible to get maximum value out of it"
		}
